    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.10.28"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">28</fw>
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Mrs. Edward R. Levy<lb/> 
                    12288 Prinster <lb/>
                    St. Louis, Mo. 63141
                </fw>
                
                <dateline>April 27, 1971</dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                <p>What a thrill is was for me to see you again after so many years: Your appearance on the Dick Cavett show was a sincere pleasure.</p> 
                <p>I attended the University of Missouri from 1954-1958. The absolute highlight of my entire college career was the semester (spring '58) I took your course, "Epoch America." I treasure your inscription in my copy of Cycle of the West.</p> 
                <p>For many years I taught fifth grade. I never missed a year of reading some of your work to my students.</p> 
                <p>God bless you.</p>
                <closer><salute>Most sincerely,</salute>
                <signed>NaOma Levy</signed></closer> 
                
            </div1>
        </body>
